The second innermost planet in our solar system is almost as massive as Earth and, with a diameter of 12,100 kilometers, is almost as big.
This planet, known as the Morning or Evening, orbits the Sun in just under 225 days.
But it rotates much slower around its own axis, and one day on Venus is 243 days on Earth.
Although Venus, with a surface temperature of 460 °C and a pressure of 92 bar, does not resemble Earth, scientists assume that the two planets were formed under very similar conditions.
